ings shape the organisational system and why they prove not only necessary but even productive for organisational functioning. In doing so, she offers new ways to think about collaboration and establishes `misunderstanding' as key factor for an insight into the field of organisational research.  afunded by Technische Universität Berlin  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aCommunication in industrial relationszIndia. 0aMiscommunicationzIndia. 4aAsia. 4aCollaboration. 4aEconomic Sociology. 4aEthnology. 4aGlobalization. 4aIndia. 4aMisunderstanding. 4aMultinational Organisations. 4aSociology of Organizations. 4aWork. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aAsia.  aCollaboration.  aEconomic Sociology.  aEthnology.  aGlobalization.  aIndia.  aMisunderstanding.  aMultinational Organisations.  aSociology of Organizations.  aWork.2 aTechnische Universität Berlinefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Frontlist eBook-Package 2021z978311076731540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839458679zOpen Access7040uhttps:/